17.	#“If something goes wrong, error correcting identifies the problem and fixes it automatically or with guidance.# Error Correcting in Data Processing# 1.Removing duplicate data#2.Fixing missing values#3.Removing outliers#4.Correcting wrong formats#An outlier is a data value that is very different from the rest of the data.#It is unusually high or unusually low compared to other values.#Consider student marks: 45, 48, 50, 47, 49, 100     Most marks are around 45–50  ,100 is far away from others  ,So, 100 is an outlier
def remove_outliers(column):           Q1 = column.quantile(0.25)         #Calculates the 1st quartile (25%)   25% of the data values are below this point
 Q3 = column.quantile(0.75)         #Calculates the 3rd quartile (75%)   75% of the data values are below this point
IQR = Q3 - Q1                      #Computes the Interquartile Range    Measures the spread of the middle 50% of the data
threshold = 1.5 * IQR              #Sets the outlier limit The value 1.5 × IQR is a standard rule to detect 
outlier_mask = (column < Q1 - threshold) | (column > Q3 + threshold)     #Creates a True/False mask  True → value is an outlier  False → value is normal
return column[~outlier_mask]       #Returns only the values that are not outliers
#The function finds very small or very large values compared to most data and removes them.
